I really want to like Party Hard Go.  It's a darkly humorous little romp through the bad part of your psyche, the part that has that point where you just think "Fk Everything!".  The gameplay is smart and the gags are worth it.  However, ATM, the wonky controls are seriously hampering an already challenging game.    The problem really only becomes an issue when trying to evade the authorities; it's almost impossible due to the habit the controls have of just... stopping.  This gets worse as a level goes on; as the police are called throughout a level, their pursuit becomes more aggressive, making your chances of capture via the lame control frustratingly likely.  If tinyBuild could just make the controls a bit more fluid I would wholeheartedly recommend PHG to anyone with an anti-social streak / twisted sense of humor they'd rather express harmlessly.  As of this writing - I recommend, but with the caveat above.  Please address, devs!
